This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with wireless sensor networks and timing synchronization. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the transmission and processing of information. The paper also touches upon cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the protocol for establishing synchronization. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with distributed beam forming. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) as it involves multiple nodes working together in a network.
